There are 2 ways   
1. dual boot (who has limited ram and cpu capacity) (temporary solution)
2. virtualization software (permanent solution)
  
virtual machine software is used for running more than 1 operating system within a computer.
#1 You need to install oracle virtualbox software on your computer
https://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/6.1.22/VirtualBox-6.1.22-144080-Win.exe
https://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/6.1.22/Oracle_VM_VirtualBox_Extension_Pack-6.1.22.vbox-extpack
  
1. install VirtualBox-6.1.22-144080-Win.exe
2. after installing virtualbox install extension pack software Oracle_VM_VirtualBox_Extension_Pack-6.1.22.vbox-extpack (enable features like shared folders, networking, sound drivers, display drivers)
  
check on your bios settings virtualization has been enabled or not. if not check with your laptop model in google/youtube how to enable virtualization at bios level.
  different laptops has different bios configuraiton and manufacturing vendors provides the details of how to enable.
    
